{"type":"FeatureCollection","features":[{"type":"Feature","geometry":{"type":"GeometryCollection","geometries":[{"type":"Point","coordinates":[142.93317713344493,-37.28291105725744]},{"type":"Polygon","coordinates":[[[142.91317858302534,-37.27813240299083],[142.91214861476735,-37.28332271111112],[142.91523851955037,-37.29056122729975],[142.92158999050176,-37.29984736028679],[142.9342929323956,-37.29984736028679],[142.94407763088273,-37.296160356466416],[142.95094408595415,-37.28769321927096],[142.95420565212254,-37.2785421771715],[142.95163073146847,-37.27102929608065],[142.93618120754428,-37.26597475422808],[142.92416491115583,-37.26734088007983],[142.91403688991605,-37.27335153938563],[142.9133502444017,-37.27622009398433],[142.91317858302534,-37.27813240299083]]]}]},"properties":{"feedType":"warning","cap":{"category":"Fire","event":"Grass Fire","eventCode":"grassFire","urgency":"Unknown","severity":"Unknown","certainty":"Observed","contact":"lily.watson-jones@justice.vic.gov.au","senderName":"Country Fire Authority","responseType":"None"},"sourceOrg":"EMV","sourceId":"42448","sourceFeed":"cop-cap","sourceTitle":"Community Information","id":"42448","category1":"Community Update","category2":"Fire","status":"Unknown","name":"Community Information","action":"Stay Informed","statewide":"N","location":"Ararat","created":"2026-07-22T16:38:00+10:00","updated":"2026-07-22T16:38:02+10:00","webHeadline":null,"webBody":"<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px\">This <b>Community Information&nbsp;</b>is being issued for&nbsp;<span title=\"warning_locality\" class=\"param\" contenteditable=\"false\">Ararat</span>.<div><div><ul><li>There is a grassfire caused by a green waste burnoff at <span title=\"warning_incident_location\" class=\"param\" contenteditable=\"false\">Port Fairy Road, Ararat</span>.</li><li>Smoke will be visible from nearby communities and roads.&nbsp;</li></ul></div></div></div><div style=\"font-size: 120%; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom:20px\">There is no immediate threat to the community and\nno action is required. </div><div style=\"margin-bottom:20px\"><div>This message was issued\nby <span title=\"warning_issuing_agency\" class=\"param\" contenteditable=\"false\">Country Fire Authority</span>. </div><div><br></div><div><b>Unless the situation changes, this will be the last message issued for this fire</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><ul><li>Smoke information: Smoke can affect people’s health. For more information visit: https://www.betterhealth.vic.gov.au/health/videos/Smoke-and-your-health-protect-your-health.&nbsp; Anyone experiencing wheezing, chest tightness and difficulty breathing should call Triple Zero (000).</li></ul></div><div><br></div><b>Use multiple sources to stay informed:&nbsp;</b><div><ul><li><a href=\"http://emergency.vic.gov.au/respond/\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">www.emergency.vic.gov.au</a>.</li><li><a href=\"https://vicemergency.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/articles/115001055007-What-is-the-VicEmergency-Hotline-\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">VicEmergency Hotline</a>&nbsp;- freecall 1800 226 226. </li><li><a href=\"https://vicemergency.zendesk.com/hc/en-gb/articles/230492607-What-is-the-VicEmergency-app-\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">VicEmergency app</a>.</li><li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/vicemergency\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\"> Facebook</a> or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/vicemergency\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a>&nbsp;(#vicfires).</li><li>Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.</li></ul></div><div><b>Accessibility:</b></div><div>The following service can help you,&nbsp;or someone you know, access information during an emergency.</div><div><ul><li>To access this information in other&nbsp;languages&nbsp;call the <a href=\"https://www.tisnational.gov.au/\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">Translating and Interpreting Services</a> on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to&nbsp;call&nbsp;VicEmergency Hotline.</li><li>If you are&nbsp;deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment&nbsp;contact <a href=\"https://www.accesshub.gov.au/about-the-nrs/nrs-call-numbers-and-links\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">National Relay Service</a>&nbsp;for assistance\nand ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.&nbsp; </li></ul></div></div>","text":"COMMUNITY INFORMATION - GRASS FIRE - Stay Informed\nIncident Location: Port Fairy Road, Ararat\nIssue Date: Wednesday 22 July 2026, 04:38 pm\nNext Update: Wednesday 22 July 2026, 07:00 pm\n\nMore details at http://emergency.vic.gov.au/respond/#!/warning/42448/moreinfo\n\nThis Community Information is being issued for Ararat.\n- There is a grassfire caused by a green waste burnoff at Port Fairy Road, Ararat.\n- Smoke will be visible from nearby communities and roads. \n\n\nThere is no immediate threat to the community and no action is required. \n\n","sizeFmt":null,"incidentFeatures":[{"properties":{"feedType":"incident","sourceOrg":"EMV","sourceId":"42448","sourceFeed":"cop-cap","sourceTitle":"Community Information","id":"42448","category1":"Fire","category2":"Grass Fire","name":"Community Information","location":"Port Fairy Road, Ararat","created":"2026-07-22T16:38:00+10:00","updated":"2026-07-22T16:38:02+10:00","webHeadline":null,"sizeFmt":null}}]}},{"properties":{"status":"Patrolled","feedType":"incident","sourceOrg":"VIC/DEECA","sourceId":817709,"sourceFeed":"deeca-burns","sourceTitle":"Mt Clay - Tower Rd","id":817709,"category1":"Planned Burn","category2":"Planned Burn","created":"2026-07-21T05:51:52.000Z","updated":"2026-07-21T05:51:52.000Z","resources":0,"size":"246.91","sizeFmt":"246.91 Ha.","url":"https://www.ffm.vic.gov.au/bushfire-fuel-and-risk-management/planned-burning-in-victoria","location":"5.5Km North Of Narrawong, Mt Clay State Forest"},"type":"Feature","geometry":{"type":"Point","coordinates":[141.6978,-38.1979]}},{"properties":{"status":"Patrolled","feedType":"incident","sourceOrg":"VIC/DEECA","sourceId":3010310,"sourc